  "text": "Our data are important because until now it is the only study that compares two biologic agents used to treat post-operative recurrence of Crohn's disease. The strength of this cohort is that it is population-based, because it encompassed all Crohn's patients treated with biologics in Romania (approx. 21 million inhabitants). An important limitation of this study, inherent to a retrospective study is non-uniformity in assessment of some outcome parameters. Giving the fact that the risk of postoperative recurrence increases over time, for a better evaluation of the preventive treatment for POR, a long term prospective open trial is recommended, such as the study conducted by Yoshida et al. [CITATION_1] showing the effectiveness of infliximab as a preventive therapy for POR in CD.",
